      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt and combine",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Grease and line a 20 x 20 cm square tin. Melt the {{dark-chocolate}} and {{coconut-oil}} together in a heatproof bowl set over a pan of barely simmering water. Stir until smooth and remove from the heat. Stir in the {{caster-sugar}}, {{oat-milk}}, and {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} until just combined. Fold in the {{chocolate-chips}} if using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake and cool, 25 to 28 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour into the tin and spread level. Bake for 25 to 28 minutes until the surface is crackled and set and the edges have begun to pull away from the tin. A skewer inserted in the centre should come out with moist crumbs, not wet batter. Cool completely in the tin before cutting (at least 2 hours). The brownies firm significantly as they cool.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
